  <discussion>Cardamine maxima has not been found with mature fruits and seeds and it has long
        been suspected to be a hybrid between C. concatenata and C. diphylla. Molecular studies (P.
        W. Sweeney and R. A. Price 2000) indicate that C. maxima is distinct from both those
        species. Although we hesitate to maintain it as a species, its wide distribution and
        morphological distinctness warrant its recognition.</discussion>
